	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><br>the above mana conversion equasion is right; here is perhaps a simpler way to figure it.<br><br>Each point of INT or WIS = lvl * .2<br><br>So at lvl 50, each extra point of Int is (50*.2) = 10 mana.<br><br>So conversly, 40 mana to a lvl 50 is worth 4 Int.<br><br><br>(At lvl 1, however, where each point of Int is (1*.2) = .2 mana, or 1 mana for every 5 points of Int, the extra 40 mana would equate to an extra 200 Int ~ which it is always better to start out with +Mana stuff at first, then switch to +int stuff later.)<br><br>Hows that for Nerdom?&nbsp;&nbsp;Math AND Video games, all rolled into one<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
